Assistant to the President for Homeland Security Dr. Liz Sherwood-Randall met with President Nana Addo Dankwa Akufo-Addo of Ghana at the United Nations to discuss efforts to counter terrorism in Africa. They participated in the UN Security Council's High Level Debate on the same topic, chaired by President Akufo-Addo. They also discussed deepening the U.S.-Ghana partnership at the upcoming U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit hosted by President Biden in Washington D.C. next month.